An 'Appenzeller' is a type of cheese that originates from Switzerland.
It has a pale yellow color with a smooth texture that can be either firm or semi-firm.
The cheese has a unique, pungent aroma and a strong, tangy flavor.
It is typically made from cow's milk and has a fat content of around 45%.
Appenzeller can be used in various dishes, such as fondue or grated on top of pasta.
It is often found in specialty cheese shops or gourmet markets.
Overall, 'Appenzeller' is a distinctive and flavorful cheese that is prized by cheese lovers around the world for its distinct taste and texture.
